  "Notes": [
    {
      "Text": "Security update for gnutls",
      "Title": "Topic",
      "Type": "Summary"
    },
    {
      "Text": "This update for gnutls fixes the following issues:\n\nSecurity issue:\n\n- CVE-2025-14831: excessive resource consumption when verifying specially crafted malicious certificates containing a\n  large number of name constraints and subject alternative names (bsc#1257960).\n\nOther updates and bugfixes:\n\n- update libgnutls package to avoid binder getting calculated with SHA256 (bsc#1258083, jsc#PED-15752, jsc#PED-15753).\n- lib/psk: Add gnutls_psk_allocate_{client,server}_credentials2\n- tests/psk-file: Add testing for _credentials2 functions\n- lib/psk: add null check for binder algo\n- pre_shared_key: fix memleak when retrying with different binder algo\n- pre_shared_key: add null check on pskcred\n",
      "Title": "Details",
      "Type": "General"
    },
    {
      "Text": "The CVRF data is provided by SUSE under the Creative Commons License 4.0 with Attribution (CC-BY-4.0).",
      "Title": "Terms of Use",
      "Type": "Legal Disclaimer"
    },
